<td colspan=2 bgcolor="#0000AF"><font color=white>Ok, just got one and was testing the differnce. It's very hard to tell because counting seconds as you swing has a large error rate. With my Bard I noticed about a 10% difference (estimate) I'm going to give to my Ranger (level 20) with a SSoY and see if its more noticable. At 10% the item is note worth the 15K price tag. At 20% or 25% it is though. But then again you have to add in more duel wields/ double attacks. The math being:<BR>
<BR>
8/24 SSoY becomes 8/21.6 at 10%<BR>
8/24 SSoY becomes 8/19.2 at 20%<BR>
8/24 SSoY becomes 8/18 at 25%<BR>
<BR>
Knowing Verant it is more like 5%-10% 8-/<BR>
<BR>
Anybody notice a major difference? I have not yet. I am assuming its only 10%.</font></td></tr></table>
